&lt;p&gt;In the UK, we operate in one of the most competitive and fast-paced restaurant markets, where success requires strong execution, resilience, and commercial drive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Mandarin-speaking KAM Hunter to accelerate TheFork’s growth within the Asian restaurant segment, with a strong focus on the Chinese restaurant market across key UK areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a target-driven new business role, focused on acquiring high-potential independent restaurants, groups, and strategic accounts in the Chinese sector. You will take full ownership of your territory, build a strong self-generated pipeline, and lead negotiations end to end within one of the UK’s most dynamic and influential hospitality communities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;👉&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.careers.thefork.com/&quot;&gt; Discover life at TheFork&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a field-based role (approx. 70% of your time).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your day-to-day will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prospecting and acquiring new restaurants, with a strong focus on Chinese and wider Asian restaurants in key UK locations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generating your own pipeline through cold calls, walk-ins, referrals, networking, and local market mapping&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conducting in-person meetings and product demos to present TheFork’s B2C and B2B value proposition&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing your own pipeline from first contact to negotiation and closing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adapting your schedule to restaurant availability, including occasional evening meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sharing market insights with the wider sales team to improve our approach to the Asian restaurant segment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What success looks like:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;First 60 days&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Quick ramp up on the sales pitch and product knowledge (both B2C and B2B)Create a strong pipeline of qualified opportunitiesDemonstrate consistent daily activity across&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;calls, visits, meetings, and follow-upsClose your first 10+ deals independently&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;After the first 60 days&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reach full productivity on quarterly acquisition targets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage your territory independently and proactively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consistently generate new business through your own pipeline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver strong weekly activity levels, including around 10 meetings per week and 30+ new opportunities created monthly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Become a key internal reference point for the Chinese and wider Asian restaurant segment in your territory&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt

